access: My Entire apartment will be yours.
description:
My apartment is prefect for large family or large groups. Spacious living area and private bedrooms. Half a block from the subway leaving all of Manhattan easily accessible. Great cafe's, restaurants, and shops within walking distance. Local grocery store, fresh fruit stands and markets  open days and nights.

4 Bedrooms in the lively neighborhood of East Harlem in Manhattan.
Beautifully furnished space with large rooms.
WIFI and  cable equipped. 
Easy access in and out of NYC.
1 block to the 6 Train on 116th street and one stop to the 4, and 5 train on 125th street.

Tons of bars, restaurants, pubs, lounges and night life attractions.
Walking distance to Central Park and The Museum Mile.
Diverse ethnic restaurants in walking distance. Delivery is also available. 
Located near all major highways, expressways, and bridges into The City.

This is a spacious apartment offers 4 bedroom 1living room 1 bathroom and a kitchen. In total 1400 square feet (or 130 square meter). There are 5 beds: 4 queen sized beds and 1 queen size sofa bed, great fit for 10 guests.

Kitchen:  has a full line of pots and utensils, toaster, coffee maker, electric kettle, microwave, oven, and a full size fridge.

 Bathroom: fresh towels and linens, and shower necessities (soap, shampoo, conditioner, body wash).

Other amenities: Internet, hair dryers, ironing boards, and educated and resourceful host.

My Entire apartment will be yours.

As often as needed, I typically respond to messages within an hour.

East Harlem (El Barrio or Spanish Harlem, if you prefer) is growing accustomed to receiving visitors. This neighborhood’s vibrant roots are depicted through its large-scale murals, discussed in its museums, and revered by its members. The draw of its deep seeded traditions is matched by superb subway accessibility. Although East Harlem is gaining notoriety as a neighborhood to watch, it’s still raw at its core—especially after sunset.

6 Train: 4 minutes by foot 
Laguardia Airport: 15 minutes by cab without traffic
JFK Airport: 30 minutes by cab without traffic
Wall Street / Financial District: 31 minutes by subway
Times Square: 15 minutes by subway

Check in is at 2:00 pm & check out is at 11:00 am please keep this in mind when booking your flights. YOU WILL BE SUBJECTED TO A LATE CHECK-IN FEE IF YOU ARRIVE PAST 8:00 PM
